@startuml current_004_save_load_roundtrip
title UC Life Sim — save / load round-trip (SAVE_VERSION = 4)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"

actor "caller\n(autosave / SystemMenu)" as C
participant "save/index.ts" as SV
participant "active world\n(via Proxy)" as W
participant "ship + space worlds\n(via getWorld)" as WX
participant "sim/scene + clock + loop" as SIM
participant "ecs/spawn\nresetWorld + spawnNPC" as SPAWN
participant "idb-keyval\n(superjson)" as IDB

== saveGame(slot) ==

C -> SV : saveGame('auto' | 1..3)
SV -> SV : refuse if clock.mode === 'combat'
SV -> W  : query(EntityKey) → snapshotEntity
SV -> WX : snapshotShip() + snapshotSpace()
SV -> W  : snapshotRelations
SV -> IDB : set(bundleKey + metaKey)

== loadGame(slot) ==

C -> SV : loadGame(slot)
SV -> IDB : read bundle
SV -> SV : reject on version / seed mismatch
SV -> SIM : stopLoop()
SV -> SPAWN : resetWorld()  (rebuilds *every* scene from data + seed)
SV -> SIM : useScene.setActive(target)\nor migratePlayerToScene(target)
note right
  Bumps swapNonce → ScopedRoot
  remounts <App>, killing useQuery
  hooks that were orphaned by
  world.reset().
end note
SV -> W  : index byKey via query(EntityKey)
SV -> SPAWN : spawnNPC(...) for missing immigrants\n(keys 'npc-imm-*')
SV -> W  : destroy entities not in saved keys
SV -> W  : overlay each EntitySnap → 18 traits
SV -> W  : restoreRelations(byKey, relations)
SV -> WX : restoreShip / restoreSpace (v3+ / v4+)
SV -> W  : mark every Character Active\n(load auto-pauses, no activeZone tick yet)
SV -> SIM : clock.setState(speed:0, mode:'normal')
SV -> SIM : startLoop()
SV --> C  : { ok: true }

note over SV
  (CONCERN) save/ couples to:
   - sim/loop, sim/scene, sim/clock
   - ecs/spawn, ecs/world
   - getWorld('playerShipInterior')
   - getWorld('spaceCampaign')
   - systems/{combat, population,
     relations, engagement} reset hooks
  Every new system with module-level
  state costs save/load coverage. A
  "world reset lifecycle" event would
  invert this.
end note

@enduml
